@card  

Totally going to animate it with [Karn's Touch](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Karn's Touch), let it hold a [Runed Stalactite](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Runed Stalactite), then attack. Once blockers are declared, [MOONMIST](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=MOONMIST)! HA! And you thought I was just trying to bash you for 8! (that's an exclamation mark, not 40320) Alternately [Xenograft](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Xenograft) to Humans, which is also good for [Angelic Overseer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Angelic Overseer) and [Ludevic's Test Subject](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ludevic's Test Subject) (w/ Moonmist).  

P.S. @Standard: [Xenograft](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Xenograft), [Tezzeret, Agent of Bolas](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tezzeret, Agent of Bolas), and [Moonmist](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Moonmist).  
\_  

@Bazzoka  

You know what's cool about EDH? You can do whatever the hell you want if your playgroup lets you. It's still primarily a casual format, and even if it weren't *you could still play it casually*! :D  
\_  

@phyrexiantrygon  

I hope the people you play EDH with will let you! It sounds like fun. :D  
\_  

@majinara  

